Hapl-O-mat v 1.0 03/16/2016

General information
-------------------
Hapl-O-mat is software for HLA haplotype inference via an
expectation-maximization algorithm. It supports processing and
resolving various forms of HLA genotype data.


The latest version
------------------
The latest version can be found on the Github server under
INSERT URL.

 
Installing under Linux
----------------------
Installing Hapl-O-mat requires a C++ compiler with C++11 support.
Hapl-O-mat is compiled via a Makefile (g++ as default compiler):

    make
    make clean


Usage
-----
For a quick guide on Hapl-O-mat and some tutorials please see file
GETTING STARTED.


